title: captain marvel thoughts
body:
so I went to see Captain Marvel on Monday, and I really enjoyed it! I was not expecting to have this many feelings about Carol/Maria, but here we are. I have so many.

Obviously, happy shippy feelings ABOUND because holy crap, there are so many moments of sweet chemistry and mutual support between them. But I also feel a bit betrayed/sad about it.

It is so McFucking Intense for Carol to be presumed dead, and then come back with no memories, and then discover that she has a life partner and a child she helped raise, and then remember (some of?) life with them, and then need to leave them again at the end. Did she stay gone for the next… 20 years? Possibly!! We don’t know, and we might never know. Can you imagine the emotional distress? The convoluted grieving processes with no opportunity for closure? For Carol? For Maria? for MONICA??

That’s intense in a way that I feel the movie did not honor, because it would not acknowledge the depth of the relationships that it created. The movie was good at creating a sense of sweetness and real home, but not good at portraying the full weight of the commitments attached to becoming family with another person! Especially a child! Her zooming off into space at the end felt like actual tragedy to me, but it wasn’t framed that way in the movie.

And on one hand, I am tempted to blame heterosexism for this problem. (Like, whether Carol and Maria smooch or not, Carol and Maria and Monica are explicitly stated to be family to each other. And their family does not fit into a heteronormative definition of nuclear family, so the movie, like much of the world, sees it as less binding/valid/important than it would a hetero-married-with-children-genetically-related-to-both-parents one.) On the other hand, the MCU didn’t give Clint’s family any consideration either, so maybe they are just bad at thinking about families in general.   ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

So many of my feelings about this ship are wrapped up in meta-feelings about the franchise, and how its inconsistent writing/selective amnesia are almost definitely going to forget all about Maria and Monica and not acknowledge how hugely fucking sad that is. 

I thought my expectations for Marvel writing had been lowered enough to protect my heart, but apparently they were not. :/

anyways, I took all my feelings and made a bootleg-footage vid with them. you can watch it here if you’re interested
